    <header>
        <div class="header-container">
            <h1>Baretos Baratos</h1>
            <a href="/+Ocio.leaf">
                <img src="/Images/BaretosBaratos/masOcio.svg" alt="Logo +OCIO" class="header-logo">
            </a>
        </div>
        <p>Revolutionizing Zaragoza's Consumption with Smart Technology</p>
    </header>

    <!-- Introduction Section -->
    <section>
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
            In my quest to explore new ways of generating passive income with minimal human intervention, 
            I embarked on an innovative project that combines artificial intelligence, graphic design, and e-commerce. 
            The central idea is to create an application that centralizes all leisure activities in Zaragoza, 
            allowing users to do everything from ordering a taxi to purchasing drink packages at affiliated venues.
        </p>
        <p>
            With this premise, Baretos Baratos was born, an app focused on bars and nightlife, which after several design iterations 
            and business expansion, rebranded into +OCIO, an app that could encompass all kinds of activities and services one could request 
            and/or desire during their free time.
        </p>
    </section>
    <!-- Concept and Ideation Section -->
        <section>
            <h2>Conceptualization and Design</h2>
            <p>
                Everything began with an intense phase of research and experimentation.
                The goal was to create a solution that not only appealed to local users in Zaragoza,
                but also one that was efficient and modern. Using Zaragoza's open API,
                I was able to integrate real-time information on taxis, buses, and other basic services.
            </p>
            <p>
                For the interface design, I used software like Figma and Adobe XD to prototype screens
                and define the user flow. Each screen was carefully optimized to provide a frictionless user experience,
                both in light and dark modes.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Features Section -->
        <section>
            <h2>Main Features</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Real-time bus and taxi schedules.</li>
                <li>Purchase of drink packs and exclusive offers at affiliated venues.</li>
                <li>Special promotions in local bars and restaurants.</li>
                <li>Light and dark mode to suit the user's visual preferences.</li>
                <li>Integration with Zaragoza's open API for reliable and updated information.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- App Development Process Section -->
        <section>
            <h2>Development Process</h2>
            <p>
                The development of the application required careful planning and execution.
                I opted for an agile approach, using SwiftUI for interface design and Vapor for backend management.
                The main goal was to minimize manual intervention, utilizing automated processes to manage transactions,
                real-time notifications, and integration with the Zaragoza API.
            </p>
            <p>
                Services like Firebase were also integrated for user management and authentication,
                and Stripe for pack and promotion purchases, facilitating the flow of money between users and venues.
            </p>
        </section>

