            </p>
            <embed src="/pdfs/OcioZaragozaLogoDesign.pdf" width="600" height="400" type="application/pdf">
        </section>

        <!-- Conclusion Section -->
        <section>
            <h2>Conclusion</h2>
            <p>
                Baretos Baratos is the perfect solution to maximize the leisure experience in Zaragoza. Thanks to the integration of real-time data, local promotions, and a personalized visual experience, this app becomes an indispensable tool for leisure lovers in the city. Download it now and start enjoying!
            </p>
            <p>
                However, during the business feasibility study, we encountered legal obstacles that affected payment management. The business model relied on charging a small percentage of each sale, but adding the percentage of the banking integration or payment gateway, plus the 21% VAT, made the scheme unprofitable. Furthermore, not being able to operate as a legal commission agent, services would have to be invoiced, adding another layer of complexity.
            </p>
            <p>
                The problem worsened by not being able to hold payments in our accounts until the end of the month to then transfer the corresponding part to the client. This model would have generated distrust among venues, affecting their cash flow. On the other hand, collecting the total and then invoicing them would have resulted in the perception that we were deducting money they had already acquired.
            </p>
            <p>
                For all these reasons, and due to the limitations of current Spanish legislation, it was concluded that the business model was not economically viable.
            </p>
